# OpenClaw cron template for CurveLens.
#
# This is intentionally an agent turn, not a plain system cron command:
# - the Python pipeline collects, normalizes, computes features, and formats
#   the daily brief + alert messages
# - the OpenClaw curvelens agent fetches the Akamai-protected CME bulletin,
#   runs the pipeline, and delivers the messages via its own Telegram integration
#
# A bare `python agent/run_pipeline.py` in system cron is NOT sufficient:
# nothing would fetch the CME bulletin (bot-protected) or deliver Telegram —
# both require the agent, per AGENTS.md Runtime Model.
#
# Runs every 30 minutes in the T+1 early-morning retry window. Each firing uses
# the headed Playwright downloader to capture the CME "current" bulletin and
# read its internal date, then only processes it if that date is new
# (notify.py --is-new gate); a firing that finds an already-handled date stays
# silent, so repeated firings never duplicate Telegram sends.
# Ships --disabled with a telegram:YOUR_CHAT_ID placeholder — fill in the real
# chat id and enable deliberately. Do not commit a working chat id here.

openclaw cron add \
  --agent curvelens \
  --name "CurveLens daily brief" \
  --cron "*/30 2-6 * * 2-6" \
  --tz "America/New_York" \
  --session isolated \
  --message "From /path/to/CurveLens, read AGENTS.md Runtime Model and follow it exactly. This cron reruns every half hour across the early-morning window; never duplicate Telegram by using the freshness gate below. First run the headed Playwright downloader exactly like this: CME_BULLETIN_RUN_PIPELINE=0 CME_BULLETIN_DIR=/path/to/CurveLens/ccvm/data/cme_bulletin /Users/openclawyi/.openclaw/workspace/skills/cme-bulletin-downloader/scripts/download_cme_bulletin_pdf.js . If the download fails, finish CME_PDF_UNAVAILABLE and send nothing. Parse the downloader JSON with Python; use its date field as <pdf-date> and path field as the saved PDF path. Run ccvm/.venv/bin/python agent/notify.py --is-new <pdf-date>. If is_new is false, run/send nothing and finish CME_PDF_NOT_NEW. If is_new is true, run ccvm/.venv/bin/python agent/run_pipeline.py --date <pdf-date>. On ERROR, stop and report which step failed. On OK, run ccvm/.venv/bin/python agent/notify.py --prepare --date <pdf-date>, then ccvm/.venv/bin/python agent/notify.py --list-pending, and deliver each item's text verbatim (Markdown) via OpenClaw Telegram to telegram:YOUR_CHAT_ID — PRIORITY_ALERT first, then DAILY_BRIEF. After each successful send, ack only that id with ccvm/.venv/bin/python agent/notify.py --ack <id>. Parse JSON with Python, not jq. Do not fabricate market data or run --force-pdf without approval." \
  --model "openai/gpt-5.5" \
  --thinking low \
  --timeout-seconds 900 \
  --no-deliver \
  --disabled
